---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Email and SMS in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for coordinated email and SMS journeys, consent, frequency control, and measurable ecommerce lifecycle marketing.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Data-rich omnichannel programs','Useful for coordinated segments, events, and channel rules.','Cost and governance grow with profiles and sends.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/sms'],['Omnisend','Commerce-first email and SMS','Designed for merchants that want common ecommerce triggers across channels.','Review SMS economics and message limits carefully.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/sms-marketing/'],['Sequenzy','Focused lifecycle sequences','A good fit when email is the primary channel and SMS is used deliberately at key moments.','Confirm SMS support and regional compliance needs.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','Broad marketing operations','Useful when campaigns, automation, and transactional communication share one stack.','Shopify event depth may require integration QA.','https://www.brevo.com/features/sms-marketing/'],['Shopify Email','Native email-first teams','Simple for stores that want reliable email without a complex channel matrix.','SMS orchestration is not its central strength.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Email and SMS should share customer context without becoming two copies of the same interruption. Pick the platform that can enforce consent, channel priority, quiet hours, and frequency caps.</p><p>Evaluate incremental orders, opt-out rates, complaint signals, and margin by channel. A larger send count is not a strategy; the useful question is whether SMS adds value that email alone would not provide.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for email and SMS</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> The best programs assign a job to each channel: email can explain and merchandise, while SMS can handle genuinely time-sensitive reminders. {a[0]} is worth testing when its segmentation and suppression rules can keep those jobs distinct. Start with one journey, define a control group, and document consent and quiet-hour behavior.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Check current email contacts, sends, SMS credits, country coverage, and automation limits before forecasting cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Need</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Channel coordination</td><td>Shared events and suppression</td><td>Incremental conversion</td></tr><tr><td>Compliance</td><td>Consent and quiet-hour controls</td><td>Opt-outs and complaints</td></tr><tr><td>Profit</td><td>Per-channel attribution</td><td>Contribution margin</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Read <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, review <a href="/use-cases/segmentation">segmentation use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
